  "text": "Several animal studies have shown that treatment with tamoxifen does not only reduce the promotion of radiationinduced mammary tumors [CITATION_1] ), but also seems to reduce the initiation of radiation-induced mammary tumors (for review see [CITATION_2] . This observation would confirm the hypothesis that the interaction of tamoxifen and XRT might take place at the cell cycle checkpoints. The augmentation of the radiation-induced cell cycle arrest by tamoxifen treatment would facilitate DNA repair and thus prevent radiation-induced genomic instability.",
